China Sets up New Cellular Engineering Institute XI'
The Xi'an Cellular Engineering Project Development Center was
officially inaugurated today in this capital of northwest China's
Shaanxi Province. The state- designated institute is expected to
invigorate China's bio- engineering research.
Jointly founded by the No. 4 Medical College of the Chinese People's
Liberation Army and the Shaanxi New and High-Tech Industries Investment
Co., the center will focus on the study of engineering development of
animal cells, cross-breeding tumor cells, cellular-engineering and cell
factor tests.
The institute, funded with venture capital from the investment company,
will become an incubator for important bio-engineering programs and
play a role in transforming scientific research into products.
